Can I open a Virgin Money bank account online? Absolutely! You can apply for a new transaction or savings bank account easily through the app, or join online – it just takes six simple steps and you’re done. If you’ve opened a Go transaction account, we’ll send you a Virgin Money Visa debit card in the mail, and you’re ready to start earning points towards epic rewards. What do you need to open a bank account? To open a new bank account with us you’ll need to be over 14 years of age, have an address in Australia, and send us at least one form of Australian ID – so we can confirm you are who you are. This could be something like your drivers’ licence or passport. Then you’re good to go. Join through the Virgin Money app, or open an account online . How do I open a joint bank account with Virgin Money? When you apply to open an account online or through the Virgin Money app, you can select if you’re apply for a joint account. We’ll then send a message to the person you want to open an account with, and the account will be opened once they’ve provided their details, including identification details. We’ll let you know when your account is open and ready to go. Can I open a bank account without going into the bank? Yes!
